        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:34PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles north of Standish, or 19 miles southeast of Termo, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Lassen
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
